Sequel to the extremely limited 50th Anniversary Collection: 1962 (AKA Copyright Extension) set, released late last year, will again be made available in limited quantities. This time is will be released on vinyl only.

The 50th Anniversary Collection is a series of two albums by Bob Dylan, released 27 December 2012 and 2 December 2013.
The albums feature studio and live recordings from respectively 1962 and 1963. Sony released only 100 copies of the four-CD set for the first volume or six-LP set for the second volume in Europe.
The sets are released to prevent the recordings from entering the public domain.
